South Africa's Luther Singh and Jamie Webber missed their spot kicks, handing Madagascar the victory. JOHANNESBURG - Bafana Bafana failed to advance to the Cosafa Cup semifinals on Sunday, losing 4-3 on penalties to Madagascar. The quarterfinal match, played at the Peter Mokaba Stadium in Polokwane, ended 0-0 after 90 minutes and headed into a penalty shootout. South Africa's Luther Singh and Jamie Webber missed their spot kicks, handing Madagascar the victory. Madagascar will take on Zambia in the semifinals of the competition while South Africa will play Namibia in the Plate semifinals.